# InfluxDB Data Deletion

## Purpose

This command deletes data from the InfluxDB bucket based on a specified time range and filter criteria.

## Delete Command

```bash
curl --request POST "https://influxdb.renewgrid.in/api/v2/delete?org=Ramtaranga&bucket=Ramtaranga" \
  --header "Authorization: Token <TOKEN>" \
  --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
  --data '{
    "start": "2024-02-01T00:00:00Z",
    "stop": "2026-06-01T00:00:00Z",
    "predicate": "_measurement=\"wattmon_std_mv\" AND dlid=\"9C956E78E37A\""
  }'
```

## Parameters

| Parameter | Description                                            |
| --------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |
| org       | InfluxDB organization name                             |
| bucket    | Bucket from which data will be deleted                 |
| start     | Start time of the deletion range (UTC)                 |
| stop      | End time of the deletion range (UTC)                   |
| predicate | Filter condition used to identify records for deletion |

## Example

The above command deletes all records that satisfy:

* Measurement: `wattmon_std_mv`
* DLID: `9C956E78E37A`
* Timestamp between `2024-02-01T00:00:00Z` and `2026-06-01T00:00:00Z`

## Verification Query

Before deleting data, verify the affected records:

```flux
from(bucket: "Ramtaranga")
  |> range(start: 2024-02-01T00:00:00Z, stop: 2026-06-01T00:00:00Z)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r._measurement == "wattmon_std_mv")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r.dlid == "9C956E78E37A")
```

## Notes

* Data deletion is permanent.
* Ensure a backup is available before running the delete operation.
* A successful request typically returns HTTP status `204 No Content`.
* Deleted data may take a short time to disappear from query results.
